<TEXT>
a detective was shot to death monday by 
his former business partner in a police fundraising business 
authorities said the gunman was killed by shots fired by the 
mortally wounded detective 
the gunman had also apparently killed his wife earlier police 
found her body in their home when they went to tell her that her 
husband was dead said police lt paul saucedo 
detective norman montion died of gunshot wounds suffered in the 
shootout with richard stratton in the office of police officers 
promotions inc authorities said 
two office employees were wounded one seriously 
stratton and montion both 42 were owners of the company and 
had a fallingout when montion was bought out by stratton 
witnesses said the company raises money for the el paso police 
officers union and the sheriffs office 
police chief john scagno said stratton spent monday morning in a 
bar where he brandished his weapon in front of bar patrons before 
heading to the office police believe he had already shot his wife 
by that time 
stratton went to the office that afternoon and fired three shots 
at montion who was sitting at a desk the police chief said 
stratton shot one employee then another who tried to knock him 
down 
police believe stratton was going to fire at the fallen montion 
again when the detective pulled his 38caliber pistol and fired 
six shots hitting stratton at least four times 
montion a 16year veteran was on duty at the time police said 
they did not know why he had stopped by his business 
police found the body of strattons wife elva corona stratton 
about four hours after the office shooting stratton left behind 
two brief notes apologizing to family members for what he was about 
to do police said 
