<DOCNO> AP891016-0003 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
editors note julie wards charred remains were found in a 
sprawling gane reserve in september 1988 four months into her 
vacation in kenya her father is convinced she was murdered the 
government claims she was eaten by wild animals chege mbitiru and 
didrikke schanche have covered the case and this is their report 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
one of the few things not contested during 
the inquest into julie wards death was that the young british 
tourist was killed in one of the worlds most famous wildlife 
preserves 
just how she was killed remains a glaring question 
chief magistrate joseph mango has promised to rule oct 27 
whether enough evidence exists to open a murder investigation into 
the 28yearold womans death 
the inquest largely the result of pressure from ms wards 
father john ward has run intermittently since midaugust ward a 
successful hotelier from suffolk england has vowed to pursue the 
case whatever mango decides 
ms ward a wildlife photography enthusiast was four months 
into her second trip to kenya when she disappeared sept 6 1988 in 
the sprawling southwestern masai mara game reserve 
seven days later following an air and ground search ms wards 
suzuki bush vehicle was found mired in a creek well off her 
intended route six miles away in trackless bush searchers found 
the young womans lower jaw and charred and severed lower left leg 
near a pile of ashes and partly burned personal belongings 
kenyan police said ms ward either committed suicide or was 
eaten by one of the many carnivores that inhabit the game reserve 
home to kenyas largest lion population 
john ward insists his daughter was murdered and he has spent 
hundreds of hours and tens of thousands of dollars trying to prove 
it 
ward and his attorney byron georgiadis dismiss the suicide and 
wild animal theories as absurd they claim park employees and 
police engaged in a massive coverup to protect either ms wards 
murderer or kenyas lucrative tourism industry 
tourism earned kenya 360 million last year and is the nations 
largest foreign exchange earner 
georgiadis has argued that ms ward was killed by someone who 
knew the masai mara well who had freedom of movement there and who 
could have ordered or inspired a coverup 
he has accused the maras senior game warden simon makallah of 
involvement in the death 
makallah found ms wards remains within hours after the suzuki 
was located and georgiadis claims he was able to do that only 
because he already knew where they were he further claims the game 
warden planted ms wards vehicle in the creek 
mr makallah knew where her remains were and was going there 
to make sure that nothing was left but he was with others so when 
he saw some still remained he had to find them georgiadis said 
in a closing argument oct 5 
to have committed suicide he said ms ward would have had to 
hack off her left leg cut off her head and douse her own remains 
with gasoline before setting them alight 
the wild animal theory was rejected after pathologist reports 
both in kenya and britain determined ms ward had been dismembered 
with a sharp instrument and her remains subsequently burned say 
ward and georgiadis both reports determined she died sept 12 
1988 
however the kenyan report prepared by state pathologist dr 
adel yousef shaker which initially said ms wards remains had 
been cleanly cut and that she suffered a sharp wound was 
subsequently changed by a superior 
the altered report said instead that her remains had been 
cracked and torn injuries more indicative of an animals 
mauling 
this report proved a key point during the inquest georgiadis 
claimed shaker was forced to accept the changes 
accepting the altered report as true said state prosecutor alex 
etyang left no other possible conclusion than that ms ward died 
by misadventure implicitly endorsing the wild animal theory 
etyang denied there had been any sort of coverup but he 
admitted police may have been inefficient and incompetent in their 
investigation 
superintendent muchiri wanjau a police investigator on the 
case admitted several blunders including the failure to take 
statements from rangers present where ms ward last was seen or 
from a swiss film crew camped several hundred yards from where her 
vehicle was found 
he also failed to record statements made by maasai tribesmen 
camped a mile from where ms wards remains were found and who 
georgiadis said told police they heard a womans screams 
in addition to the altered postmortem report and police 
failures in the case georgiadis points to the forgery committed by 
a game park gate keeper david nchoko who wrote ms wards name in 
his visitors book the day she was supposed to have left the 
preserve 
the visitors book with ms wards signature would have been the 
only material evidence the young woman left her campsite as 
intended but confronted with a handwriting experts testimony that 
her signature had been forged nchoko admitted he entered it into 
the book himself he said ms ward had forgotten to do so 
the fact that he forged and lied brings into question the 
whole edifice of the assertion that she left sand river gate on 
sept 6 said georgiadis 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP891016-0004 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
it only took a threeday meeting for 
the communists to scrap their party but it could take years to 
remove the influence of more than four decades of communist rule in 
hungary 
the communist party formally the hungarian socialist workers 
party was declared dead at a historic congress a week ago that 
gave birth to the hungarian socialist party 
spurred by upcoming free elections the congress heeded 
reformers calls for a party with democratic aspirations that would 
be more appealing to the electorate than a monolithic 
marxistleninist party the elections are due by june 
reform has been in the wind in hungary for the past several 
years even before mikhail s gorbachev decreed changes in the 
soviet union 
the most blatant stalinist manifestations personality cults 
workers brigades a repressive secret police were done away with 
under the late janos kadar but real reform gathered steam only 
after kadar was retired last year after 32 years at the helm 
the collective leadership succeeding kadar decided 
liberalization was the only way to counter serious economic 
problems it permitted political opposition to flourish for the 
first time since the communists consolidated power in 1948 and it 
pledged to permit the countrys first free national elections in 41 
years 
such developments have placed hungary on the vanguard of 
democratization within the soviet bloc along with poland the first 
warsaw pact country with a primarily noncommunist government 
the old party decided in september to begin dismantling its 
government chapters and the ministries of the interior finance 
and trade and commerce already have been formally depoliticized 
the party formally transferred control of its armed workers 
militia to the government in the summer 
after more than four decades of rewritten history there are 
plans to write it again this time reflecting events independent 
of marxist coloration education minister ferenc glatz has urged 
history teachers to use their own judgment in the classroom instead 
of old party dictates 
dozens of independent newspapers and periodicals have blossomed 
and are as free with criticism of the government and the party as 
any in the west private radio a britishhungarian commercial 
venture began functioning in june 
yet old habits die hard 
the premier and all but one of his ministers were ranking 
members of the old party and most remain in the top levels of the 
new one 
about 85 percent of senior officials in the interior ministry 
which controls the police were communist party members according 
to the independent weekly heti vilaggazdasag in the ministry of 
trade and commerce the rate is 80 percent and in the finance 
ministry it is 73 percent 
top management at state enterprises continues to be appointed by 
the party through the government the classic decisionmaking 
triangle of management party and trade union officials never has 
been dissolved although party spokesman emil kimmel said in an 
interview that it has died a natural death 
the congress endorsed the right of the new hungarian socialist 
party to organize politically in the workplace dismaying reformers 
who associate such a presence with traditional marxistleninist 
infiltration and indoctrination 
the overwhelming majority of workers militia members are also 
party members and its marxistleninist orientation continues 
informally 
plans to correct school text distortions could be complicated by 
reluctance in the new party to face the past squarely while 
condemning stalinist excesses the party congress rejected calls by 
reformist delegates to declare a holiday in memory of the 1956 
antistalinist revolution it expressed support instead for a 
day of reconciliation a normal working day with no direct 
mention of the soviet blocs bloodiest revolt 
the major newspapers radio stations and television remain 
under direct or indirect party control 
with the hungarian socialist party committed at least on paper 
to democracy and market forces its founders assert that its 
creation moves the country farther along the path of reform 
but membership is open to anyone who signs a declaration of 
agreement with the new partys democratic nature leading to fears 
that conservatives will join to keep jobs or privileges if enough 
do so their sheer numbers could sabotage reforms 
and even if the new party turns out to be a truly democratic 
institution that honors its pledge to give up power if defeated at 
the polls the stubborn legacy of the old party is bound to color 
society for years 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
george jahn is a native of hungary and has 
covered eastern europe for the associated press for several years 
he currently is based in vienna 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

