<TEXT>
the west german publishers 
association awarded czech playwright vaclav havel its annual 
peace prize but the human rights activist was not allowed to 
leave his country to claim it 
swiss actor and director maximillian schell collected the award 
at a ceremony sunday in st pauls cathedral because prague 
authorities refused to let the 53yearold havel to travel to 
frankfurt 
havel is banned from publishing in czechoslovakia and has been 
repeatedly jailed for his role in pressing for democratic reforms 
in his communist homeland he is a cofounder of the charter 77 
human rights organization 
the west german publishers association peace prize is awarded as 
part of the annual frankfurt book fair 
the publishing group says havel plans to use the 13000 prize 
money to start an independent publishing house for banned 
czechoslovak authors 
schell read a short acceptance message sent by havel who 
decried the continued repressions in czechoslovakia against writers 
who speak out for change 
havel reminded the gathering of the risks involved for him and 
other writers living in a country where one is still thrown in 
jail for his words and where socialism has become a rubber 
truncheon 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

