<TEXT>
in a papal pilgrimage filled with 
guarded gestures none stood out more than the east timor kiss 
it underlined the tightrope pope john paul ii walked as he 
toured indonesia the worlds most populous moslem country for 
five days before reaching this indian ocean island 
the pope treaded softly when he touched on such controversial 
issues as human rights the roman catholic churchs position 
against contraception or pressures on catholics from moslem 
extremists 
but nothing provoked more debate than whether john paul kissed 
the ground of east timor the former portuguese colony invaded and 
annexed by indonesia in 1976 
john paul has kissed the ground each time he arrived in a new 
country on his 44 foreign tours 
indonesian authorities were relieved when he made no such move 
upon arriving in east timor they had posted billboards beside the 
airport tarmac welcoming him to indonesias 27th province 
although the vatican like the united nations doesnt 
officially recognize the indonesian claim on east timor john 
pauls hosts viewed his stop as bolstering their position 
but 90 minutes later when the pope arrived at a dusty seaside 
field to celebrate mass he knelt beneath the altar and kissed a 
crucifix resting on a pillow on the ground 
applause rang out from the crowd of 100000 people indicating 
people believed he had done the deed or had he 
a vatican official rushed to tell reporters that kissing the 
crucifix was merely a pastoral gesture done by every bishop 
when he enters a new diocese 
for kikus corner a frontpage column in the englishlangauge 
indonesia times the pope kissed the soil only once upon arriving 
in the indonesian capital of jakarta 
its thus a recognition of east timor as part of the 
indonesian country no doubt about it kiku told his readers 
the vatican insists that no obstacles were placed in the popes 
way during the trip and that he spoke with absolute freedom 
but he clearly made choices as he has on past trips when for 
example the price of visiting paraguay was a meeting with the 
former authoritarian ruler gen alfredo stroessner 
one such choice according to a vatican official was not to 
upset the delicate balance in indonesia which unites some 200 
ethnic and language groups 
for this reason the explanation goes john paul did not visit 
ancient buddhist and hindu temples in java near where he 
celebrated mass he also didnt step inside a model mosque when 
visiting a miniature reconstruction of indonesia in jakarta 
expert knowledge was required to decipher the codewords in his 
speeches the pope spoke of traditional practices and other 
contemporary social influences contrasting with church teaching 
on the family an apparent reference to polygamy and the 
governments active familyplanning program 
one thing john paul could not escape was the heat on his 10day 
pilgrimmage that took him from indian summer in seoul south korea 
to sweltering indonesia and mauritius 
the fairskinned pope born 69 years ago in the cool of poland 
reddened from standing hatless in open cars waving to the crowds 
temperatures were in the 90s 
the pope returned to rome today the eleventh anniversary of his 
election as pontiff 
