a car bomb exploded early today near the 
offices of a newspaper in the city of bucaramanga killing two of 
the papers workers and injuring at least seven others police said 
the director of the vanguardia liberal newspaper said in a live 
radio broadcast that drug traffickers were responsible for the 
bomb which exploded in a car parked near the offices and was 
packed with up to 130 pounds of dynamite 
the newspaper is the main daily in bucaramanga 175 miles north 
of bogota 
although i cant identify the perpetrators i can say that 
basically they are the same group of drug traffickers that have 
carried out these types of attacks in the past alejandro galvis 
ramirez said on the national radio chain caracol 
the blast killed a night watchman and a maintenance worker at 
the papers downtown offices a bucaramanga police spokesman said 
in a telephone interview 
it injured another seven people and caused extensive damage the 
spokesman said he added that 15 houses nearby were affected and 
three of them were almost completely destroyed 
police initially estimated the damage caused by the explosion at 
12 million the area is a mess the spokesman said 
the attack is the second major bombing of a colombian newspaper 
since the government began a crackdown on drug traffickers aug 19 
on sept 2 the main offices of bogotas el espectador newspaper 
were targeted in a car bomb attack that injured 83 people 
journalists at the paper blamed the attack on drug lords angered by 
the papers hard line on traffickers 
