police fired tear gas and rubber bullets today 
to disperse stonethrowing students outside a high school in arab 
east jerusalem and 15 students and five policemen were injured 
witnesses and officials said 
also today an 8yearold palestinian boy died three days after 
israeli soldiers shot him during a demonstration in the occupied 
gaza strip 
forty palestinians were detained in the east jerusalem 
disturbance which took place as thousands of religious jews 
visited jerusalem for the eightday sukkot festival police 
spokesman uzi sandori said 
the unrest began when students from the rashadiyeh high school 
blocked roads with rocks and showered police with stones witnesses 
said paramilitary border police fired tear gas and rubber bullets 
to disperse the crowd they said 
sandori said five policemen were slightly injured from stones 
officials at mukassed hospital in east jerusalem said about 15 
students were treated for teargas inhalation and bruises from 
rubber bullets 
