<TEXT>
here at a glance are highlights of actions 
taken monday by the supreme court 
 
antitrust 
 
the court agreed to decide whether states and possibly private 
citizens may use federal antitrust law to break up corporate 
mergers 
the court said it will hear arguments by california officials 
seeking to scuttle the 25 billion merger of the lucky and alpha 
beta supermarket chains 
todays action kept in effect an order issued by justice sandra 
day oconnor in august that blocks completion of the merger 
the case is california vs american stores 89258 
 
larouche 
 
the court turned away an appeal by a political action committee 
linked to fringe presidential candidate lyndon larouche it now 
faces having to pay 27 million in contemptofcourt fines 
the justices without comment refused to hear the national 
democratic policy committees challenge to fines stemming from a 
federal mail fraud and conspiracy prosecution 
the case is national democratic policy committee vs us 
89320 
 
union dues 
 
the court rejected an appeal by a righttowork group that 
sought to limit the power of unions to collect dues from 
nonmembers 
the court without comment refused to hear arguments in an 
illinois case that the group was treated unfairly by a federal 
appeals court 
the cases are national right to work foundation vs afsme 
89287 and gilpin vs afscme 89292 
 
pan am 
 
the court refused to free pan american world airways from having 
to pay 951500 plus interest to two families of 1974 crash victims 
the justices without comment left intact the awards stemming 
from the april 22 1974 crash in indonesia of a pan am plane 
flying from hong kong to los angeles all 96 passengers and 11 crew 
members died in the accident 
the case is pan am vs causey 89157 
 
penalizing lawyers 
 
the court agreed to provide some guidelines for penalizing 
lawyers who file improper lawsuits 
the court said it will hear an appeal by a washington dc law 
firm penalized 21402 for filing an antitrust suit based on 
inadequate research 
the case is cooter amp gell vs hartmarx corp 89275 
 
videotaped answers 
 
the court agreed to consider reinstating the drunken driving 
conviction of a pennsylvania man videotaped answering policce 
questions about his height weight and color of his eyes 
the court said it will decide whether police violated the 
motorists rights when they videotaped his responses before warning 
him of his right to remain silent or have a lawyer present 
the case is pennsylvania vs muniz 89213 
 
inheritance taxes 
 
the court backed out of deciding whether the internal revenue 
service when assessing inheritance taxes may challenge deductions 
state courts have allowed for legal fees and executors commission 
the justices agreed last february to decide the issue in an 
appeal by a new york lawyer who acted as executor and attorney for 
a 450000 estate 
the case is white vs us 88928 
