<TEXT>
the grammrudman deficitreduction law was 
scheduled to trigger 161 billion in federal spending cuts on 
monday following the failure of congress and president bush to 
agree on a plan to cut the governments budget deficit 
what the grammrudman law is passed in 1985 and amended two 
years later the law sets a series of declining targets for 
projected deficits for each fiscal year culminating in a balanced 
budget in 1993 the cuts are triggered automatically if the targets 
are exceeded 
why the cuts are being made grammrudman requires the cuts to 
be made oct 16 if the projected deficit for fiscal 1990 which 
started oct 1 surpasses 100 billion by more than 10 billion 
the white houses office of management and budget projected the 
deficit monday to be 1161 billion 
has it happened before twice in 1986 117 billon were 
imposed in january and remained in effect through september the 
end of the fiscal year in 1987 23 billion in reductions were 
imposed in october and were rolled back in december 
how this years cuts are applied half to defense half to 
domestic programs or 805 billion to each because the cuts are 
from different dollar totals that calculates to 43 percent cuts 
in defense and 53 percent in domestic programs 
what programs are affected all defense programs except for 
money owed in contracts many domestic programs are exempted 
including social security many other benefit programs and 
payments on the national debt certain other programs such as 
medicare can be sliced no more than 2 percent 
examples of cuts defense programs cut from 2914 billion to 
2833 billion foreign aid from 163 billion to 158 billion 
science and space from 137 billion to 133 billion agriculture 
from 188 billion to 182 billion transportation from 291 
billion to 285 billion education and social services from 382 
billion to 375 billion health from 566 billion to 562 
billion 
what the public will feel very little initially because of the 
many exemptions and because agencies have the flexibility to shift 
money around within programs many people believe most citizens 
will not notice anything at all for several weeks 
how long the cuts last technically they took effect 
temporarily oct 1 by law they were invoked permanently monday 
but congress can pass legislation at any time rolling them back 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

