from around the country the speech will appear in this weeks 
issue of seek truth the party magazine 
xinhua did not explain the delay in releasing the speech which 
may have been due to disagreement within top party ranks over how 
far to go in carrying out the crackdown on dissent the crackdown 
is part of a hardline backlash to the spring prodemocracy 
protests that were crushed by the army in june 
many rank and file party members in cities expressed sympathy 
with the protests and some took part former party chief zhao 
ziyang was accused of supporting the protests and ousted from 
office along with several top allies but the party has yet to deal 
with many zhao supporters who remain in place 
xinhua quoted jiang as saying in his speech that to ensure the 
purity of the party it is necessary to uncover the opportunists 
especially those in leading positions within the party but he 
did not identify them and xinhua gave no further information 
jiang also said the role of party cells should be strengthened 
and that exploiters a traditional word for wealthy private 
businessmen should be barred from the party because it is the 
vanguard of the working class 
the party has stepped up its emphasis on class identification 
and class struggle since june private businesses were allowed to 
make a comeback in the past decade under senior leader deng 
xiaopings policy of reforming the centralized economy and the 
party had preached that it was acceptable for some people to get 
rich at least one millionaire was admitted to the party 
since june however the party has denounced unequal 
distribution of wealth and accused businessmen of evading taxes 
and breaking other laws 
in the initial stage of socialism various economic sectors 
are allowed to coexist with the sector under public ownership 
being predominant xinhua quoted jiang as saying but we should 
not attach undue emphasis to the individual and private economies 
for they can only be a supplement to the public economy 
in its weekend resolution the beijing party committee also 
banned socalled exploiters from its ranks and urged a stronger 
party role at the workplace 
the disclosure of jiangs speech shows that the beijing 
committees actions are not those of a radical fringe but 
represent decisions of the party center 
government spokesman yuan mu meanwhile said he was confident 
that economic relations between china and the west will resume 
developing despite western censure of chinas crackdown on dissent 
no country in the world can deny that socialist china with a 
population of 11 billion stands like a giant in the east it 
is impossible for anyone to isolate china he said in an 
interview with japans kyodo news agency his comments were carried 
by xinhua 
japan and most western countries condemned the chinese armys 
attack on the protesters in which hundreds and perhaps thousands 
were killed japan initially froze its aid to china but said last 
month it was gradually resuming work on existing projects 
yuan continuing chinas policy of trying to discourage japan 
from forming a united front with the west on human rights demands 
said japans actions hurt relations but that china had noted 
differences between japans stand and that of the west i hope 
the current unpleasantness will only be a shortlived episode he 
said 
yuan spoke more harshly of the united states again accusing it 
of interfering in chinese affairs by condemning the crackdown he 
said it was up to the united states to take the first step in 
restoring friendly relations 
yuan said the partys top policymaking body the central 
committee will meet to make decisions on overcoming economic 
disorder but did not give a specific date he said it may meet 
late this month or early in november 
there has been speculation the party could announce a decision 
on any further action against zhao at the session some hardline 
leaders are believed to be pressing for his expulsion from the 
party and trial 
</TEXT>
