<TEXT>
the dow jones industrial average managed a 
rebound today defying fears of a black mondaystyle crash in some 
of the heaviest trading in the history of the new york stock 
exchange 
the dow average which represents stock prices of americas 30 
biggest industrial companies closed 8812 points higher at 
265738 a gain of 343 percent or nearly half the loss posted on 
friday 
the leap came after the average gyrated in early trading 
starting with a decline of about 63 points shortly after the 
opening bell 
most of the stocks that comprise the dow average were posting 
gains as investors snapped up bluechip issues other stocks lagged 
behind 
the nyses composite index of all its listed common stocks 
recovered its early loss and was up 421 to 18977 at the close 
but big board losers led advancing issues by a 5to4 margin at the 
close with 942 down 766 down and 286 unchanged 
the dow jones average had plunged 19058 points on friday in the 
worst decline since the 508point black monday crash of oct 19 
1987 some had feared today would be a rerun of that monday two 
years ago because it had been preceded by a sharp 100pluspoint 
drop in the dow the previous friday 
analysts were encouraged that the market avoided that scenario 
