<TEXT>
cornel wilde whose fabled career on the big 
screen spanned nearly 50 years and included an academy award 
nomination for a song to remember died of leukemia monday 
just three days after he turned 74 
wilde who had been undergoing treatment at cedarssinai medical 
center since sept 2 died with his son cornel wilde jr at his 
side said hospital spokeswoman paula correia 
wildes career on the screen and as a producer and director 
included work in more than 50 movies and stretched from 1940 to 
1987 in 1945 he was nominated for an academy award for his 
performance in a song to remember in which he portrayed 
composer frederic chopin 
i realized long ago that i could not depend on luck to bring 
me success wilde once said i worked hard extra hard to 
improve my chance by increasing my abilities and my experience it 
was my goal to accomplish in my life something of value and to do 
it with selfrespect and integrity 
wilde was born in new york city on oct 13 1915 and moved a 
year later with his parents and sister to budapest hungary where 
his father a perfume and cosmetic importer reported for duty as a 
captain in a calvary unit 
in 1920 the senior wilde obtained passports to return his 
family to the united states in 1931 the son entered columbia 
university as one of its youngest undergraduates a short time 
later his fathers ill health forced the family to return to 
europe for a time 
back in the united states and enrolled in a premedical 
curriculum at columbia wilde became a prospective member of the 
1936 us olympic fencing team but he chose to drop medicine and 
fencing to pursue acting 
wildes swordsmanship came in handy later though especially 
in stage roles like that of tybalt in romeo and juliet on 
screen he put his talent to use in a thousand and one nights 
at swords point california conquest and condors nest 
personally one of his most successful roles was as the fearless 
trapeze artist in cecil b de milles the greatest show on 
earth but he was best known for his roles in adventure movies 
that included the naked prey high sierra the bandit of 
sherwood forest beyond mombasa omar khayyam 
constantine and the cross and the fifth musketeer 
the 1955 movie the big combo which he produced and starred 
in was criticized at the time for what some considered excessive 
violence 
you cant get away from violence in drama wilde responded 
if you do not have conflict you do not have drama if a brutal 
scene is shown for no reason except to shock then it is bad 
he also acted in directed and produced beach red storm 
fear devils hairpin maracaibo sword of lancelot 
and sharks treasure wildes last movie was my very wilde 
life filmed in 1987 
wilde married actress patricia knight in 1938 they had a 
daughter wendy and divorced in 1951 he married actress jean 
wallace that year and had a son he and miss wallace were divorced 
in 1980 
funeral arrangements were pending 
