<TEXT>
jan p syse who became norways prime 
minister on monday is a bright witty eloquent and capable lawyer 
who calls himself just a boy from the country 
but many easygoing norwegians view him as a bit too polished and 
urbane 
standing for the first time as party leader in an election syse 
failed to galvanize the electorate and his conservative party came 
out of the sept 11 vote with its worst showing in 20 years 
but syse patched together the three centrist nonsocialist 
parties in a coalition to replace gro harlem brundtlands labor 
government which also experienced its worst election since world 
war ii 
the contrast between the two leaders in the public mind goes 
deeper than politics 
mrs brundtland is known abroad as a stateswoman 
environmentalist and champion of womens rights in norway she is 
simply known as gro 
the new prime minister is normally referred to as syse proper 
but formal 
the 58yearold attorney usually appears controlled measured 
and reserved mrs brundtland a 50yearold physician and 
harvardeducated public health specialist has a fiery temper but 
also will openly show grief 
syse is an excellent speaker philosphical and funny he is a 
relatively moderate politician said bernt ole aardal of the 
institute for social research 
syse became chairman of norways second largest party upon the 
sudden death of rolf presthus in january 1988 when the party was 
in the midst of a structuring crisis he had little time to 
establish his leadership before the elections aardal noted 
critics call syse a tough and clever politician strong on 
lawandorder and moral issues but he is burdened with his image 
he is seen as what norwegians would call too oslo west 
meaning that hes from the wealthy part of town very high society 
and implying that he is above other people said aardal 
born on nov 25 1930 syse was in fact raised on the pastoral 
island of notteroey south of oslo he stresses his rural 
upbringing even after almost 40 years in the capital 
i really have trouble comprehending this resilient myth that 
im so urbane said syse i am a country boy from noetteroey 
but his heavyrimmed glasses flawless diction and rigid posture 
enhance the image of an intellectual an oslo newspaper joked that 
syse would wear a tie with his towel in parliaments sauna 
syses quest for a folksier image has sometimes backfired 
he invited news media to record him fishing from a trawler this 
summer and ended up with a giant hook through his finger removed 
in a highly publicized effort involving a hacksaw and pliers 
the son of a dentistlocal politician and his school principal 
wife syse was politically active early on and was elected chairman 
of the conservative students association in 1952 he earned a law 
degree from the university of oslo in 1957 
he began his career as a lawyer for a shipowner later working 
in nonpolitical upperechelon government jobs he married teacher 
else walstad in 1959 and has two sons one who also is a politician 
he trod a familiar path through party ranks and was elected to 
parliament in 1973 
political scientist gunnar vogt said syse may prove to be a 
surprisingly strong leader as demonstrated by his ability to 
stitch together a coalition from three deeply divided parties the 
conservatives the christian peoples party and the center party 
mrs brundtland became norways first woman prime minister in 
1981 and at 44 its youngest her first term lasted seven months 
she returned to power in may 1986 and gained international 
stature as head the un world commission on the environment and 
development norwegians prefer her international record to her 
domestic one 
mrs brundtland quickly set some new rules eight of the 18 
cabinet ministers were women and her labor party made it a rule 
that each sex must have at least 40 percent of all party positions 
syses 19member cabinet also has eight women 
</TEXT>
