with the nobel peace prize 
the dalai lama arrived at new delhis international airport just 
past midnight and was greeted by cheering men women and children 
from the 100000member tibetan community exiled in india 
inside the airports arrival lounge monks in maroon and saffron 
robes lined up to welcome the 54yearold dalai lama with low bows 
and traditional gifts of white scarves outside thousands of 
tibetans lighted incense sticks and covered the roadway with 
marigold and rose petals 
i feel the award is recognition of my sincerest motivation 
for nonviolent action the leader of tibets resistance to 
chinese rule told reporters i feel it may help to create more 
awareness for the value of compassion and nonviolence 
when he was awarded the prize in oslo norway on oct 5 the 
dalai lama was in california on one of the us visits he makes at 
least twice a year to minister to buddhist faithful and to heighten 
international awareness of the tibetan struggle he spent four 
weeks in the united states on this trip 
the dalai lama fled to india in 1959 after an abortive uprising 
against the 1951 chinese annexation of his remote himalayan nation 
he has set up a governmentinexile in dharamsala an indian town 
300 miles north of new delhi 
in recent months he has dropped demands for complete tibetan 
independence and has proposed that china retain responsibility for 
military and foreign policy 
so far there has been no concession by china the beijing 
government has said it is willing to discuss tibet however it 
insists tibet must remain an integral part of china 
asked whether his receiving the 1989 nobel prize could alter 
beijings stance the dalai lama said at the moment i dont 
know but after a few months you may see something he did not 
elaborate 
china has condemned the award as an insult and interference in 
its internal affairs 
the dalai lama dressed in the sleeveless robes of an ordinary 
buddhist monk and wearing a rosary on his left wrist said he had 
still not decided what to do with the awards 469000 cash prize 
i may contribute something for the starving people in africa 
or create an institution for world peace he said i need some 
more ideas i will speak to my colleagues 
