have been forced to stay in the departments offices during the 
day said dambra 
she estimated an average of five children per night dont know 
where they will sleep stephan h lieberman the departments 
assistant director of community resources said the caseload of 
those up to age 21 who need placement has grown 8 percent to 10 
percent yearly or about 200 children a year ranging from new 
children in the system to those kicked out of other programs 
there also has been a decrease in the number of foster homes 
dambra said 
