enunciated before congress earlier this month by david f 
lambertson deputy assistant secretary of state for east asian and 
pacific affairs 
unfortunately absent a viable political process the 
cambodian factions are likely to turn increasingly to military 
means to resolve their conflict a result most likely to benefit 
the khmer rouge lambertson told the senate foreign relations 
committee on oct 2 
the united states remains unalterably opposed to a return to 
dominance of this abhorrent group which left a legacy of brutality 
and depravity from its reign of terror in the 1970s he said 
a durable settlement in this conflict must be constructed to 
ensure that the khmer rouge can never regain control and subject 
the cambodian people once again to the horrors of the past he 
said 
