president bushs 79 billion war on drugs in the 
united states has raised official fears in western europe that 
cocaine barons will broaden their alreadyexpanding market on the 
continent some officials say terrorists may be drawn into the 
lucrative trade to finance their own causes 
so far the streets of europe have been largely spared the 
