<TEXT>
tired of watching movies at home because they dont have the 
same punch as the ones at the local cinema 
you can build a high quality theater at home where your family 
and friends can enjoy a real cinemalike experience and you dont 
have to be a millionaire to finance an entertainment room fitted 
out with thoughtfully selected basics 
the basic components of a home theater are a large screen 
monitorreceiver hifi vcr andor laser videodisc player and a 
quality audio system with surrounding sound 
depending on your tastes and pocketbook a complete home theater 
could cost a few thousand dollars or soar onto the megabucks scale 
it took me several years to finance and build my system 
since my theater room is relatively small i decided that a 
27inch sony monitorreceiver would do the job 
the only video source driving the screen is a magnavox videodisc 
player because im a collector of classic and blockbuster motion 
pictures i also have a vcr which i use on a portable tv in another 
room to view rental tapes once ive made up my mind i want a movie 
for my collections i buy a copy in the high quality disc format 
the audio system consists of an onkyo tx51 receiver 43 watts 
per channel a separate 10band graphic equalizer pioneer audio 
tape deck fisher dolby surround sound decoderamplifier 30 watts 
per channel a pair of magneticallyshielded speakers at the front 
of the room and a pair of surround speakers hung from the ceiling 
at the rear of the room 
since i had to place the front speakers near the 
monitorreceiver i bought magnetically shielded ones to prevent 
picture distortion 
the final result from this mixed bag of electronic components is 
a theaterlike experience in my own home 
the dolby surround sound decoder makes the jets in top gun 
sound like theyre soaring right past you it also puts the viewer 
right in the middle of the action in the barroom fight in raiders 
of the lost ark 
many of the other movies and concerts in my collection were 
processed with dolby sound tracks for added ambience and less 
distortion 
if you havent heard a surround sound processor on home video 
try one out at a local dealer it just may surprise you a note 
for unsuspecting consumers the processor must have a licensed 
dolby circuit to decode those hidden sound tracks on a tape or 
disc dont settle for a cheaper unit which only manufactures a 
surround mode look for the dolby logo on the component or ask the 
salesperson 
with the monitorreceiver offering more than 450 lines of 
horizontal resolution the picture achieved from the disc player is 
superb 
simply put my home theater gets the job done 
when selecting your components ask for a full instore 
demonstration since speakers are considered the heart of the audio 
system take some time to shop around for them be certain they fit 
your exact needs before investing in them 
if purchasing a large screen television or monitorreceiver 
consider the signal sources you will use at home for instance if 
you are using a standard vhs hq videocassette deck then insist 
that the salesperson give you a demonstration using a vhs hq deck 
those big screens can be made to look extremely impressive in 
stores when laser videodisc players ed beta or super vhs decks are 
driving them 
save yourself the trouble and disappointment of lugging a big 
set home if it will not perform as you expected 
there are a lot of audio components offered at varying prices on 
todays market 
select what is right for you and your pocketbook stay away from 
the frills if you wont use them select quality brand name audio 
components 
</TEXT>
