<TEXT>
the stock market historically has been regarded as a barometer 
and forecaster of economic health so any severe selloff always 
provokes anxiety many economists say singleday behavior in the 
market is difficult to interpret but if stocks continue to drop 
then investors and consumers could become fearful and stop spending 
money possibly leading to a recession 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
after black monday oct 19 1987 the nations major stock and 
futures exchanges voluntarily began cooperating to avoid panicky 
selling that could cause similar collapses in the future 
their reforms include coordinated circuit breaker halts in 
trading when the dow jones industrial average falls 250 points or 
the standard amp poors 500 futures contract declines 12 points a 
special hot line crisis communication system among exchanges 
shared surveillance and audit trail information expanded computer 
capacity to handle heavy trading and special priority to 
individual investors during days of heavy market volatility 
</TEXT>
