blue chip stocks bounded ahead monday in one of 
the busiest trading sessions ever but share prices of many other 
companies trailed behind 
the dow jones average of 30 industrials knocked down by a 
powerful selling wave in the opening minutes of trading rallied as 
buyers flocked to the market to snap up bargains and helped wall 
street avoid a repeat of the black monday crash two years ago 
the barometer comprising some of the countrys best known 
companies surged 8812 to 265738 it was the fourth largest 
pointgain in the history of the dow jones industrial average 
