<TEXT>
two of japans smaller automakers 
formally entered the ranks of american transplants monday when 
subaruisuzu automotive inc dedicated its auto assembly plant 
fuji heavy industries ltd which owns a 51 percent share in the 
operation will produce its subaru legacy sedans and station wagons 
here while isuzu motors ltd which owns 49 percent will turn out 
pickup trucks and sports utility vehicles 
some auto industry analysts have expressed doubts about sias 
ability to compete with established transplants such as honda and 
nissan but neither that skepticism nor stormthreatening skies 
diminished a celebrative mood 
gov evan bayh headed the dignitaries at the ribboncutting 
the dedication ceremony commemorates the crosscultural 
relationship between sias two parent companies and the citizens of 
indiana tippecanoe county and greater lafayette said sia 
president tamon yamamoto 
the 550 million 23 millionsquarefoot facility at the 
intersection of interstate 65 and indiana 38 currently employs 
1000 including 60 japanese managers and coordinators employment 
is forecast to reach 1700 by mid1990 as sia approaches full 
production under its first phase and eventually 3200 
under the first phase sia said it should produce 60000 subaru 
cars and 60000 isuzu trucks annually plans call for expanding 
production to at least 200000 vehicles and possibly 240000 
yearly sia officials have said the sia plant is the only 
automobile assembly facility in the united states where two 
completely different product lines are built under one roof using 
the same workforce yamamoto said in prepared remarks 
sia received an 86 million incentive package that included 55 
million in state funds which bayh had criticized as too generous 
in his gubernatorial run a year ago however after his november 
election he and lt gov frank obannon visited sia executives and 
reaffirmed the states commitment to the project 
impact studies project that the plant will generate 39 million 
in local payroll dollars and more than 1 million in state taxes 
sia said 
we are proud of sias evolving role in the states economy 
executive vice president masahara masumitsu the chief financial 
officer said at a news briefing 
the plant is purchasing many of its parts in state including 
steel from northwest indiana transmissions from muncie computers 
from kokomo and glass from evansville 
we consider sia a partnership a blending of peoples 
masumitsu said 
the teamconcept philosophy sia executives espouse means the 
united auto workers wont be welcome at sia vice president james 
woroniecki head of human resources said sias starting pay for 
production workers ranges from 1160 to 1305 per hour with a 
benefits package similar to those at other japanese transplants 
management personnel have the same benefit package as hourly 
employees he said 
as for unions woroniecki said we dont think theyre 
necessary 
ninety percent of the employees hired locally come from within a 
60mile radius of lafayette and just 2 percent are from out of 
state woroniecki said one fifth of the workforce is female and 7 
percent are minorities he said 
sia as the smallest and latest of the japanese transplants may 
face the most uncertain future especially with the disappointing 
sales of the legacy which was introduced earlier this year 
